1. what is the diff btn .net and .net core
Platform:
.NET Framework → Windows only
.NET Core → Cross-platform (Windows, Linux, macOS)

Open Source:
Framework → Mostly closed
Core → Fully open-source

Performance:
Framework → Slower
Core → High performance

Deployment:
Framework → Single system-wide version
Core → Side-by-side, self-contained apps

Hosting:
Framework → IIS only
Core → Kestrel, IIS, Nginx, Apache, Docker

Updates:
Framework → Minimal updates
Core (.NET 5+) → Actively developed and future direction
